s%2A>. The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SqlDataSource.FilterExpression%2A> of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SqlDataSource> is applied anytime the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SqlDataSource.Select%2A> method is executed to retrieve data. In this example, the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SqlDataSource.FilterExpression%2A> contains a placeholder for a filter parameter, which is contained in the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SqlDataSource.FilterParameters%2A> collection. In the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.SqlDataSource.Filtering> event, the filter parameter is displayed in a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Label> control.  \\n  \\n [!code-cs[System.Web.UI.WebControls.SqlDataSourceFiltering#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_142_1.aspx)]\\n [!code-vb[System.Web.UI.WebControls.SqlDataSourceFiltering#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_142_1.aspx)]\"\n  syntax:\n    content: public delegate void SqlDataSourceFilteringEventHandler(object sender, SqlDataSourceFilteringEventArgs e);\n  inheritance:\n  - System.Delegate\n  platform:\n  - net462\nreferences:\n- uid: System.Delegate\n  isExternal: false\n  name: System.Delegate\n"}